This is equivalent to finding the number of non-negative integer solutions to the system: x11 + x12 + x13 = 0 (row 1) x21 + x22 + x23 = 1 (row 2) x31 + x32 + x33 = 2 (row 3) x41 + x42 + x43 = 3 (row 4) x11 + x21 + x31 + x41 = 1 (column 1) x12 + x22 + x32 + x42 = 2 (column 2) x13 + x23 + x33 + x43 = 3 (column 3) This is a linear programming problem with integer solutions. The number of solutions can be calculated using the inclusion-exclusion principle or generating functions. Alternatively, we can use the following approach: For each column, assign the required number of ones to the rows, considering the remaining row sums. Starting with column 1, which needs 1 one. The rows available are rows 1,2,3,4 with remaining needs 0,1,2
